rComments: The best part of Dr. Zingaro is his massive Intellect. He will astonish you with Computer Science stuff and coding, and things you can use to be a programmer and make lots of money. If he was a sandwich he will would be filled with insights and a spread of butter. Because insights taste better with butter.

Dan is a remarkable professor who really shows you that anything is possible when you work hard. Tests are difficult but he does it to push you. After all, it is U of T and compsci. Dr. Zingaro is a great person and you need to take his class, but be prepared to work for your grade. Also possible to get an A when you work hard enough

He is like a beacon of light shining through a dark cloud. Dr. Zingaro talks about code like a wizard, a brilliant brilliant wizard. Most important, he makes compSci fun. He is like a shiny wizard who has the Midas touch and turns boring topics into golden glistening Gems, and he shares his nuggets with students. Dr. Zingaro is a nugget.

Dr. Zingaro is a gentleman and a scholar. He is brilliant. When compared to other profs (and there is no comparison) he reigns supreme. He makes other courses feel like playtime. He is a savvy, brilliant, exceptionally witty academic. We need more tenured profs like him! My only regret is that I had to graduate, now I just make lots of money.

Dr. Zingaro is a professional. He is the most professional of all the profs I have ever had at U of T. And U of T is a school that prides itself on excellence and making lots of money. He is a spicy meatball in the midst of bland sauceless teaching tropes. And if you can't handle the spice get out of his master chef tasty Comp Sci  kitchen!!!!!!!!!
He's the bomb diggity
He is just way too hard. I got my lowest mark of 67 in his course. Never taking his class again.
Excellent prof. Makes things very easy . Humorous and very approachable . Quick online replies to emails and forum posts

He is a tough prof! When you look at his midterms/exams and compare them to others you obviously see this. But he is also very nice and will talk to you as a friend rather than a prof. I would love to have him again.

Hard, but very helpful. Go to his office hrs and talk to him. He is very knowledgeable and down to earth. That being said, his assignments and midterms are really hard, so don't be mislead by the way he makes everything look simple and easy in lectures
Hard

He is a gentleman and a scholar, I especially like the way he makes me feel, all happy inside and happiness translates to learning in my books. I like reading lots of books too. I especially enjoyed his lengthy insightful discussion of visco theory.
An excellent prof, and an even better person. It's remarkable what he's achieved in his life.
An amazing prof! Very helpful, loves his students. I love attending his classes! He made programming so interesting for me :)

He's a really nice and helpful prof. He cares about his students and his evaluations are fair. I actually learned a lot about Python in his class and I've taken it before in high school where my teachers were actually terrible, they made me think I would never be able to code and then I met Dan!

An amazing professor, and an even better person. Loves teaching, and REALLY appreciates students that work extra hard, albeit hard work in CSC108 for a student that already had some programming knowledge prior to the course isn't exactly mandatory. He's funny too! All in all, a great semester with Professor Z.
Dr. Z is a great Dr. almost as awesome as Dr. V, his teaching style is smooth and sometimes a little spicy. He rocks!
Great prof. Very helpful. One of the best professors I have ever had. Although that he cant see, he codes like he sees everything so well!! Very friendly and humorous as well.

This was a difficult class, but I really felt like I understood programming by the end.  He's funny in class and absolutely willing to help.  The tests and assignments could be difficult.  Overall, great prof.
Best Prof I've ever had.
Enthusiastic about what he teaches. Uses good examples, and likes to joke around, while simultaneously delivering the lecture flawlessly and keeping an air of professionalism.
best prof i've had so far (1st sem)

The best prof I've had thus far in my university experience! Amazing guy, sooo helpful and willing to help anyone that's confused. I've never heard any bad comments about this prof from fellow students. Sign up for his section!!!! He's inspirational :)

Fantastic prof. Well-prepared lectures, engaging classes, always available for help, provides quick online feedback, grades fairly, well structured tests and assignments, well planned course outline, relates course material to relevant real-world events (while throwing in several absolutely useless but HIGHLY AMUSING personal anecdotes). Phenomenal
his jokes are hilarious.
Great class
Good prof.  I recommend signing up for his section.
It's a good class.
I enjoy how he conducts the class.
I and all my friends are enjoying the class so far.
Daniel is awesome!
Nice guy.  Very approachable.
Love his teaching style.
It's refreshing to have an instructor like Daniel.
I love Daniel.  He's amazing.  Very knowledgeable and helpful.
